      "commit": {
        "parents": [
          {
            "commit": "2e0cfd857cdeffc37fd959b357c4f683b6a40fd5",
            "subject": "LU-13643 mdt: add active writers counter"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Patrick Farrell",
          "email": "pfarrell@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2025-06-10 15:02:44.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Patrick Farrell",
          "email": "pfarrell@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2025-06-10 20:03:15.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "subject": "LU-13643 llite: implement concurrent write lease for mirrors",
        "message": "LU-13643 llite: implement concurrent write lease for mirrors\n\nThis patch implements concurrent write lease functionality to\nenable multiple concurrent writers on mirrored files for\nimmediate write operations to all mirrors.\n\nKey changes:\n- Add LL_LEASE_CWLCK lease mode for concurrent write access\n- Implement server-side support for concurrent write leases\n- Add automatic lease acquisition for mirrored files in\n  ll_file_io_generic()\n- Update userspace API to support new lease type\n\nThe concurrent write lease allows multiple clients to write\nto different mirrors simultaneously, enabling immediate\nmirror writes without the need for exclusive access.\n\nServer-side changes:\n- Add MDS_OPEN_CONCURRENT_WRITE flag handling\n- Implement lease compatibility checks for concurrent writes\n- Allow multiple concurrent write leases on same file\n\nClient-side changes:\n- Automatic detection of mirrored files during write operations\n- Transparent acquisition of concurrent write leases\n- Proper lease cleanup on file close\n\nUserspace changes:\n- Add LL_LEASE_CWLCK to lease mode enumeration\n- Update lease acquisition/release functions\n- Add support in liblustreapi\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nTest-Parameters: fortestonly\nSigned-off-by: Patrick Farrell <pfarrell@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: Ibe10a492c12c81c9591eca6fef05108482bcf93d\n"
      },
